  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Marcus Epigrammatic poet, Writer of epigrams, probably identical with the rhetor
    of the same name who, in the Augustan era, was a pupil of Cestius Pius, and who is described by Seneca maior as a man of
    eloquence and caustic humour (contr. 2,6,11 suas. 7,7,12 etc.). Generally, his 37 mainly erotic-sympotic epigrams
    from the ‘Garland’ of Philippus are successful and elegant variations of conventional themes..." Degani, Enzo (Bologna). 
    "Argentarius." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and
    Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2010. Brill Online. Tufts University Library. 09 December 2010 .</mads:note>
